        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The Zend_Form_Element_File getFileName($value = null) function should have an additional optional parameter which would be $path = null just like in the Zend_File_Transfer_Abstract class where the getFileName accepts a boolean (on the second parameter) which will truncate the full path if true is passed.\n\nIf value is empty, the adapter's getFileName is called and therefore Zend_Form_Element_File getFileName function should be behaving the same as the one in the abstract class.\n\nThe suggested correction would then be:\n\npublic function getFileName($value = null, $path = null)\n {\n        if (empty($value)) {\n            $value = $this->getName();\n        }\n\n        return $this->getTransferAdapter()->getFileName($value, $path);\n}"
        },
